Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[dscrd-hush] <ITM> my website (angular 7 base) in total is 400kb, the api is small and updates on blockchain.
So I have small custom chromium base version of browser, its hooks up to IPFS storage, now you visit a website(Ethereum object), the ethereum object you have links to the main IPFS object.
Now the IPFS will have links to all the contents of the website. 
It takes 10 seconds to loads up and then interacts with smart contract. (No purpose yet)
Currently I want to view news today(default view), it will check ethereum contract for any updates and then access IPFS file.
The news will load. Now I want to post a comment, it will post on ethereum against that contract. 
Last thing I have is I want to upload new content, it will upload image, call golem network to process it and the result get stored in IPFS object, the hash then gets posted to ethereum network.
